Fagrie Lakay, who was a free agent, was released by Wits this week. CAPE TOWN - Cape Town City FC have announced the signing of former Bidvest Wits forward Fagrie Lakay. Lakay, who was a free agent, was released by Wits this week. He only joined Wits from SuperSport United in January 2019 but had since been linked with a move to his hometown club, Cape Town City. The Citizens announced on their official Twitter account on Friday morning 